2
00:00:22.137 --> 00:00:25.014
<i><font color="#454545">Translated line by line from Japanese.
with great effort.</font></i>

3
00:00:25.015 --> 00:00:27.015
<font color="#005384"><font color="#00426c">UncleSubs</font></font>

4
00:00:52.263 --> 00:00:53.275
Nozaki.

5
00:00:53.276 --> 00:00:54.874
you haven't gone home yet?

6
00:00:57.269 --> 00:00:58.275
Yeah.

7
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:06.813
Are you waiting for someone?

8
00:01:06.910 --> 00:01:07.977
What?

9
00:01:09.539 --> 00:01:10.539
Well...

10
00:01:11.696 --> 00:01:12.696
Yeah.

11
00:01:14.425 --> 00:01:15.609
Got it...

12
00:01:18.219 --> 00:01:20.044
See you tomorrow then.

13
00:01:40.726 --> 00:01:43.059
She's here.
You really came.

14
00:01:45.630 --> 00:01:46.989
Nozaki.

15
00:01:48.032 --> 00:01:50.966
It's better if you stop putting
your shoes in your locker.

16
00:01:56.060 --> 00:01:57.566
No way!

17
00:01:58.120 --> 00:02:00.371
What is she going to do tomorrow?

18
00:02:00.466 --> 00:02:02.615
Seriously. you can't!

19
00:02:02.710 --> 00:02:04.709
Absolutely impossible.

20
00:02:09.919 --> 00:02:12.340
Oh. you're up for it?

21
00:02:12.465 --> 00:02:14.215
Bon voyage!

22
00:02:22.369 --> 00:02:23.777
My goodness!

23
00:02:23.872 --> 00:02:24.934
How awful!

24
00:02:25.296 --> 00:02:26.630
Disgusting!

25
00:02:30.106 --> 00:02:31.441
No way!

26
00:02:43.037 --> 00:02:44.726
Don’t look over here. you ugly!

27
00:02:44.822 --> 00:02:47.615
Nozaki. why don't you go back to Tokyo?

28
00:02:47.709 --> 00:02:49.351
We will miss you.

29
00:02:54.203 --> 00:02:57.684
I can't believe Aiba was taken
away by an ugly girl like you.

30
00:02:57.927 --> 00:03:00.837
Do you have any idea how Taeko felt?

31
00:03:02.097 --> 00:03:03.849
Do you have any idea?

32
00:03:11.390 --> 00:03:13.246
I'm so scared!

33
00:03:17.039 --> 00:03:18.800
Taeko. let's go home.

34
00:03:18.949 --> 00:03:20.953
Girls. seriously. that's boring.

35
00:03:21.050 --> 00:03:22.152
Shut up!

36
00:03:28.039 --> 00:03:29.439
Hey...

37
00:03:33.002 --> 00:03:35.121
I've already told you before...

38
00:03:35.381 --> 00:03:38.315
I really don't give a damn about Aiba.

39
00:03:40.880 --> 00:03:41.909
But...

40
00:03:45.318 --> 00:03:47.116
We get it. right?

41
00:03:47.219 --> 00:03:48.349
Yeah.

42
00:04:00.781 --> 00:04:01.865
Let's go.

43
00:04:28.558 --> 00:04:30.935
I found you! Sis!

44
00:04:45.130 --> 00:04:46.340
Shou.

45
00:04:49.819 --> 00:04:50.369
Shou!

46
00:04:52.399 --> 00:04:55.019
Shou. don't cry.

47
00:04:57.153 --> 00:04:58.369
Don't cry.

48
00:04:59.135 --> 00:05:00.250
Don't cry.

49
00:05:01.990 --> 00:05:03.369
Don't cry.

50
00:05:16.783 --> 00:05:18.664
So you mean...

51
00:05:19.009 --> 00:05:22.384
my students are bullying her?

52
00:05:24.142 --> 00:05:25.559
Ms. Minami.

53
00:05:26.055 --> 00:05:28.851
Haruka is also one of your students. right?

54
00:05:30.499 --> 00:05:32.000
Yeah.

55
00:05:33.520 --> 00:05:34.910
Why you...

56
00:05:36.619 --> 00:05:38.141
Mr. Nozaki.

57
00:05:39.642 --> 00:05:42.185
Our school is going to
be shut down this year.

58
00:05:42.871 --> 00:05:45.257
In these critical final days

59
00:05:45.353 --> 00:05:48.968
Don't you think it's better
to avoid trouble?

60
00:05:58.129 --> 00:06:00.659
<i>In this small-rural town.</i>

61
00:06:01.786 --> 00:06:06.425
<i>Including me. just a mere ten odd
students will graduate this year.</i>

62
00:06:07.232 --> 00:06:10.415
<i>Except for me. they have
been together since childhood.</i>

63
00:06:10.569 --> 00:06:12.274
<i>The future is also the same</i>

64
00:06:12.370 --> 00:06:14.949
<i>they would always be
together until they die.</i>

65
00:06:50.430 --> 00:06:52.799
GO AWAY AND DIE!

66
00:06:54.940 --> 00:06:57.040
<i>In two months...</i>

67
00:06:57.416 --> 00:06:59.417
<i>we're going to graduate.</i>

68
00:07:07.859 --> 00:07:14.869
LIVERLEAF

69
00:07:34.270 --> 00:07:35.257
Let's go!

70
00:07:35.353 --> 00:07:37.293
He deserves it!

71
00:07:47.762 --> 00:07:49.344
Ms. Minami...

72
00:07:49.782 --> 00:07:52.672
Nozaki's table looks horrible!

73
00:08:00.859 --> 00:08:02.442
Wow. just ignore us!

74
00:08:06.019 --> 00:08:07.599
Why did you do something so stupid?

75
00:08:12.507 --> 00:08:13.526
You too.

76
00:08:14.909 --> 00:08:16.662
Stop it!

77
00:08:25.366 --> 00:08:26.829
It was not her who did it.

78
00:08:28.812 --> 00:08:29.821
It was me.

79
00:08:30.476 --> 00:08:32.566
I'm the one who did it.

80
00:08:33.419 --> 00:08:34.820
Brat.

81
00:08:36.150 --> 00:08:36.969
What?

82
00:08:43.570 --> 00:08:44.409
Brat!

83
00:08:46.512 --> 00:08:47.311
What?

84
00:09:00.146 --> 00:09:01.487
Ms. Minami!

85
00:09:06.975 --> 00:09:08.316
Miss!

86
00:09:33.609 --> 00:09:34.569
Gross!

87
00:09:35.175 --> 00:09:37.296
Today. Kyon threw up again.

88
00:09:37.990 --> 00:09:39.749
Kyon is a puke teacher.

89
00:09:40.099 --> 00:09:41.203
She is throwing up!

90
00:09:41.620 --> 00:09:43.170
Then she cleans it up by herself.

91
00:09:45.019 --> 00:09:46.108
I'm home.

92
00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:47.552
Welcome home.

93
00:09:47.840 --> 00:09:48.879
Dad!

94
00:09:50.461 --> 00:09:52.041
What happened to you?

95
00:09:52.710 --> 00:09:54.059
He got beaten at school today.

96
00:10:02.156 --> 00:10:03.426
Haruka.

97
00:10:04.340 --> 00:10:06.319
Don't go to school anymore.

98
00:10:07.670 --> 00:10:09.434
You don't have to force yourself.

99
00:10:10.372 --> 00:10:14.056
We had moved to this town
because of my job.

100
00:10:15.450 --> 00:10:16.902
I'm really sorry.

101
00:10:19.409 --> 00:10:21.154
The graduation day will come soon.

102
00:10:21.715 --> 00:10:23.299
Just stay at home safely.

103
00:10:25.920 --> 00:10:29.741
I'm sure you will find good
friends in high school.

104
00:10:31.116 --> 00:10:32.119
Okay?

105
00:10:37.653 --> 00:10:40.143
Hello. Grandpa?

106
00:10:40.808 --> 00:10:41.890
Yes...

107
00:10:41.985 --> 00:10:43.397
Sister?

108
00:10:44.430 --> 00:10:46.459
She's got a fever.

109
00:10:51.088 --> 00:10:52.175
Let me see.

110
00:10:53.629 --> 00:10:56.842
You still have a fever.
just take it easy today.

111
00:10:58.800 --> 00:10:59.799
Okay?

112
00:11:06.111 --> 00:11:08.112
Sis. are you okay?

113
00:11:09.180 --> 00:11:10.295
Yeah I'm okay.

114
00:11:10.392 --> 00:11:11.742
what about you?

115
00:11:11.842 --> 00:11:12.677
Me?

116
00:11:12.795 --> 00:11:15.715
Of course I'm fine!

117
00:11:27.931 --> 00:11:29.094
Be careful on the way.

118
00:11:31.768 --> 00:11:33.610
Well. it's getting interesting.

119
00:11:33.920 --> 00:11:35.694
It looks like we are professionals.

120
00:11:35.790 --> 00:11:37.989
You can get a job with this.

121
00:11:38.329 --> 00:11:39.765
Hey Taeko

122
00:11:40.106 --> 00:11:43.006
Nozaki hasn't come to
school for three days.

123
00:11:43.319 --> 00:11:45.072
Maybe she won't come anymore.

124
00:11:46.289 --> 00:11:47.311
Who knows?

125
00:11:48.311 --> 00:11:51.468
Let's send somebody to check on her.

126
00:11:54.219 --> 00:11:56.670
We really like her. right?

127
00:11:59.079 --> 00:12:00.650
Rumi!

128
00:12:09.149 --> 00:12:10.716
Don't look this way.

129
00:12:10.899 --> 00:12:13.709
That grin of hers.
so disgusting as always.

130
00:12:15.419 --> 00:12:18.216
You should convince her to
come back to school tomorrow.

131
00:12:19.362 --> 00:12:21.197
If it doesn't work out...

132
00:12:21.322 --> 00:12:23.205
You'll be promoted to "target".

133
00:12:23.819 --> 00:12:24.600
Disgusting.

134
00:12:25.632 --> 00:12:27.417
Gross!

135
00:12:31.429 --> 00:12:34.081
And bring the "trophy" too. okay?

136
00:12:36.830 --> 00:12:40.150
You're terrible. you keep telling her
not to go to school. then to go...

137
00:12:40.292 --> 00:12:41.872
Shut up!

138
00:12:56.640 --> 00:12:59.259
Do you really have a fever?

139
00:13:02.299 --> 00:13:03.220
Yeah.

140
00:13:03.919 --> 00:13:06.900
A-Are you feeling better?

141
00:13:07.683 --> 00:13:08.350
Yeah.

142
00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:12.028
That's a relief.

143
00:13:13.536 --> 00:13:14.643
I'm sorry.

144
00:13:19.585 --> 00:13:23.909
What a beautiful song.
can I borrow it?

145
00:13:24.004 --> 00:13:24.743
What?

146
00:13:28.513 --> 00:13:29.466
Sure.

147
00:13:30.279 --> 00:13:31.752
Ah. I almost forgot.

148
00:13:40.560 --> 00:13:41.590
Stop it!

149
00:13:46.040 --> 00:13:48.278
What are you going to do
with the pictures of me?

150
00:13:50.399 --> 00:13:53.910
N-no. I’m not going to do anything…
I’m not going to do anything.

151
00:13:54.372 --> 00:13:55.909
I'm sorry.

152
00:14:09.413 --> 00:14:12.376
Nozaki. you have already recovered. right?

153
00:14:12.639 --> 00:14:15.539
Please come to school tomorrow.

154
00:14:15.739 --> 00:14:19.640
Otherwise I... get... get...
in trouble. you know?

155
00:14:20.843 --> 00:14:21.662
Trouble?

156
00:14:21.758 --> 00:14:23.445
I will be in trouble. troubled.

157
00:14:25.800 --> 00:14:29.489
But. I'm not going to
go to school anymore. so...

158
00:14:39.460 --> 00:14:40.305
What?

159
00:14:43.479 --> 00:14:44.622
No way.

160
00:14:48.816 --> 00:14:50.747
Nozaki. if you don't come to school...

161
00:14:50.849 --> 00:14:53.429
They will be targeting me.

162
00:15:02.560 --> 00:15:06.232
This CD. does it really belong to her?

163
00:15:06.570 --> 00:15:07.697
Yes.

164
00:15:07.822 --> 00:15:10.241
I... I borrowed it from Nosaka.

165
00:15:10.842 --> 00:15:12.657
If it's yours. I will kill you.

166
00:15:16.299 --> 00:15:17.591
What about Nozaki?

167
00:15:17.687 --> 00:15:19.651
Did she say anything else?

168
00:15:21.172 --> 00:15:25.834
She said we were pissing her off.

169
00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:29.423
With the sick face she had. she wanted
me to get out quickly.

170
00:15:29.520 --> 00:15:30.681
Fuck.

171
00:15:31.682 --> 00:15:34.195
You didn't get lots of loot.

172
00:15:34.439 --> 00:15:37.387
This can't be counted as evidence. right?

173
00:15:37.606 --> 00:15:39.257
I asked you to take a picture.

174
00:15:41.045 --> 00:15:42.250
In that case...

175
00:15:42.544 --> 00:15:45.404
Rumi. you will be the target.

176
00:15:45.500 --> 00:15:47.380
Congratulations.

177
00:15:52.610 --> 00:15:53.936
Taeko.

178
00:15:54.660 --> 00:15:56.975
What do we do with this CD?

179
00:16:14.696 --> 00:16:16.037
Sis. who is he?

180
00:16:16.169 --> 00:16:17.359
Your friend?

181
00:16:20.960 --> 00:16:22.819
What are you taking pictures of?

182
00:16:24.889 --> 00:16:26.048
Liverleaf.

183
00:16:26.170 --> 00:16:27.830
Liverleaf?

184
00:16:29.449 --> 00:16:33.197
This rebellious plant survives
the harsh winter...

185
00:16:33.294 --> 00:16:36.414
and blooms as if it were breaking
through the snow.

186
00:16:38.129 --> 00:16:42.074
When spring comes.
this area will be covered in liverleaf.

187
00:16:42.581 --> 00:16:44.206
Then. I can take good pictures.

188
00:16:44.825 --> 00:16:46.706
You are so cool. Big bro!

189
00:16:48.879 --> 00:16:50.266
Is she your sister?

190
00:16:50.612 --> 00:16:51.331
Yes.

191
00:16:51.427 --> 00:16:53.219
My name is Nozaki Shouko.

192
00:17:09.172 --> 00:17:11.077
This town...

193
00:17:11.704 --> 00:17:13.281
has nothing. right?

194
00:17:14.502 --> 00:17:17.553
You also transferred school like me. right?

195
00:17:18.662 --> 00:17:19.703
Yeah.

196
00:17:21.008 --> 00:17:24.359
My granma lives in this town.
so I came here by myself

197
00:17:25.090 --> 00:17:26.360
I see.

198
00:17:31.600 --> 00:17:34.389
Big bro. can you take a picture of us?

199
00:17:34.620 --> 00:17:35.695
Enough.

200
00:17:36.059 --> 00:17:36.889
Sure.

201
00:17:39.482 --> 00:17:41.765
Then stand side by side over there.

202
00:17:53.067 --> 00:17:55.867
It's the first time I take
a picture of people.

203
00:17:56.821 --> 00:17:58.625
I feel really nervous.

204
00:18:01.005 --> 00:18:01.986
Get ready!

205
00:18:30.089 --> 00:18:32.996
Taeko is an aspiring
hairdresser. right?

206
00:18:33.093 --> 00:18:35.828
And you're getting a free haircut.
what a great deal!

207
00:18:39.970 --> 00:18:41.650
It's not like that.

208
00:18:43.519 --> 00:18:46.077
Your dull hair do makes you looks gloomy.

209
00:18:49.539 --> 00:18:51.040
Ah. I see.

210
00:19:07.389 --> 00:19:09.013
What do you think. Rumi?

211
00:19:10.349 --> 00:19:11.863
Feeling refreshed?

212
00:19:13.301 --> 00:19:16.319
Y-yes...
It feels nice and light.

213
00:19:17.819 --> 00:19:19.025
I guess...

214
00:19:19.119 --> 00:19:21.218
It's not looking good. is it?

215
00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:26.807
You just needed
to bring Nozaki back.

216
00:19:28.170 --> 00:19:28.929
Yeah...

217
00:19:29.751 --> 00:19:31.251
Come on.

218
00:19:31.378 --> 00:19:34.923
Don't you hate that girl or
something like that?

219
00:19:35.062 --> 00:19:36.643
What do you think of her?

220
00:19:42.523 --> 00:19:43.866
I want to kill her.

221
00:19:45.284 --> 00:19:46.402
What?

222
00:19:49.849 --> 00:19:51.545
I want her dead.

223
00:19:54.179 --> 00:19:57.019
Wow. you look so cute in the photos!

224
00:19:57.455 --> 00:19:59.938
Hey. hey. Shoko's going too!

225
00:20:00.779 --> 00:20:02.799
Shoko can't go. no. no.

226
00:20:02.896 --> 00:20:04.284
She has homework. right?

227
00:20:05.375 --> 00:20:08.124
Come on! Dad will be home soon.

228
00:20:19.840 --> 00:20:21.379
Sister!

229
00:20:23.949 --> 00:20:26.949
Look. I did it in art class.

230
00:20:27.083 --> 00:20:29.004
I thought I would give it to you.

231
00:20:29.390 --> 00:20:30.468
Wow!

232
00:20:31.283 --> 00:20:32.963
It's so cute.

233
00:20:33.863 --> 00:20:37.916
Actually. I wanted put
in the cloverleaf. but

234
00:20:39.509 --> 00:20:40.714
Thank you.

235
00:20:44.350 --> 00:20:46.719
You two look perfect together.

236
00:20:47.260 --> 00:20:48.280
You little fool!

237
00:20:50.800 --> 00:20:51.780
I'm leaving.

238
00:20:51.959 --> 00:20:54.115
Have a nice day.

239
00:21:42.880 --> 00:21:44.176
It's so beautiful.

240
00:21:46.589 --> 00:21:49.839
If the snow comes.
the view will be more beautiful.

241
00:21:51.069 --> 00:21:52.267
It's going to snow?

242
00:21:55.079 --> 00:21:56.277
Yes. it will.

243
00:21:57.385 --> 00:21:58.773
It's almost time.

244
00:22:02.060 --> 00:22:03.169
I'm sorry.

245
00:22:05.139 --> 00:22:06.364
It's okay.

246
00:22:41.989 --> 00:22:43.148
Nozaki!

247
00:23:48.280 --> 00:23:49.609
Thank you for today.

248
00:23:50.460 --> 00:23:51.599
You are welcome.

249
00:23:52.820 --> 00:23:54.700
When spring comes.

250
00:23:54.796 --> 00:23:56.848
let's go to see the liverleaf.

251
00:23:57.372 --> 00:23:58.378
Yes.

252
00:23:58.937 --> 00:24:00.402
when spring comes around.

253
00:24:02.668 --> 00:24:04.805
Those... aren't they...

254
00:24:35.568 --> 00:24:37.458
I think there are still people inside.

255
00:24:40.129 --> 00:24:42.429
- Danger. stand back!
- Does she live here?

256
00:24:44.180 --> 00:24:46.284
They are still in there.

257
00:24:46.379 --> 00:24:48.437
What are you guys doing?
you two will die.

258
00:24:48.939 --> 00:24:50.000
Nozaki!

259
00:24:50.660 --> 00:24:52.030
Shouko!

260
00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:53.935
Dad!

261
00:24:54.030 --> 00:24:56.029
Mom!

262
00:25:03.350 --> 00:25:04.340
Aiba!

263
00:25:04.839 --> 00:25:06.045
Aiba!

264
00:25:06.139 --> 00:25:07.829
What are you doing? go back!

265
00:25:09.010 --> 00:25:10.532
There's a boy inside!

266
00:25:11.509 --> 00:25:12.718
Get out of here!

267
00:25:12.844 --> 00:25:14.553
The boy went inside.

268
00:25:16.638 --> 00:25:17.638
No...

269
00:25:19.058 --> 00:25:20.058
No...

270
00:25:43.639 --> 00:25:44.815
She is still breathing!

271
00:25:44.909 --> 00:25:46.055
Call an ambulance! Hurry up!

272
00:25:46.149 --> 00:25:47.169
Nozaki!

273
00:26:57.109 --> 00:26:58.809
Kazuo…

274
00:27:04.019 --> 00:27:05.618
your dad...

275
00:27:06.349 --> 00:27:08.704
held her tightly in his arms.

276
00:27:08.937 --> 00:27:11.521
as if he were protecting Shouko.

277
00:27:19.629 --> 00:27:21.568
Should I take it upstairs?

278
00:27:22.899 --> 00:27:24.325
Put it over there. please.

279
00:27:24.420 --> 00:27:25.235
Okay.

280
00:27:38.139 --> 00:27:39.399
Taeko.

281
00:27:40.089 --> 00:27:41.563
Thank you. mom.

282
00:27:42.719 --> 00:27:43.893
Yesterday's fire...

283
00:27:43.988 --> 00:27:46.342
looks like it was in
your classmate's house.

284
00:27:46.909 --> 00:27:49.420
It seems his parents died in the fire...

285
00:27:49.929 --> 00:27:51.328
That's a shame.

286
00:27:53.129 --> 00:27:56.197
Let me know when the class
is collecting money for the funeral.

287
00:27:56.507 --> 00:27:57.592
Right.

288
00:28:02.460 --> 00:28:03.625
What's wrong?

289
00:28:05.280 --> 00:28:07.167
Nothing. I'm leaving.

290
00:28:20.839 --> 00:28:22.646
If they find out. it's over.

291
00:28:23.850 --> 00:28:26.321
We'll be arrested.

292
00:28:27.909 --> 00:28:29.520
Calm down. calm down.

293
00:28:29.949 --> 00:28:31.833
No one saw. there is no evidence.

294
00:28:31.929 --> 00:28:33.264
Didn't you burn your hand?

295
00:28:33.360 --> 00:28:35.558
Isn't that evidence?

296
00:28:36.519 --> 00:28:37.719
It's not like that.

297
00:28:38.600 --> 00:28:40.690
Are you guys scared?

298
00:28:41.699 --> 00:28:42.851
Because...

299
00:28:43.680 --> 00:28:45.100
we killed someone.

300
00:28:45.658 --> 00:28:46.777
Oh yeah.

301
00:28:47.496 --> 00:28:49.258
This all is Kuga's fault.

302
00:28:49.768 --> 00:28:50.917
Hold on.

303
00:28:51.180 --> 00:28:52.754
But. you know...

304
00:28:52.850 --> 00:28:55.895
I only planned to scare her a bit.
I didn't think it would go too far.

305
00:28:56.969 --> 00:29:01.241
The way the group leader freaked out...
I was honestly a bit scared.

306
00:29:02.089 --> 00:29:03.374
However...

307
00:29:05.603 --> 00:29:07.538
Taeko wouldn't say
anything to anyone. right?

308
00:29:07.639 --> 00:29:09.197
Taeko's fine.

309
00:29:09.609 --> 00:29:12.634
I'm more worried about
these two than her.

310
00:29:16.610 --> 00:29:17.543
Hey.

311
00:29:18.079 --> 00:29:19.745
Stop crying.

312
00:29:20.940 --> 00:29:23.220
If my parents know. I...

313
00:29:24.510 --> 00:29:26.410
I will die.

314
00:29:43.149 --> 00:29:44.519
Hey Taeko.

315
00:29:45.540 --> 00:29:47.479
Have you heard the story?

316
00:29:48.460 --> 00:29:50.815
After you left...

317
00:29:51.211 --> 00:29:53.115
it was amazing!

318
00:29:53.209 --> 00:29:55.259
I wish you'd seen it.

319
00:30:02.959 --> 00:30:05.815
Could you please not touch my desk?

320
00:30:15.469 --> 00:30:18.969
I want you to stop going out
with Taeko until graduation.

321
00:30:21.425 --> 00:30:23.359
They hate you. don't they?

322
00:30:26.240 --> 00:30:28.895
I want you to graduate
with good feelings.

323
00:30:29.950 --> 00:30:31.844
We don't want any trouble.

324
00:30:35.340 --> 00:30:36.804
Miss...

325
00:30:38.469 --> 00:30:39.490
Yes?

326
00:30:42.119 --> 00:30:44.215
For you...

327
00:30:45.190 --> 00:30:48.394
what is Taeko to you?

328
00:30:49.680 --> 00:30:51.326
What do you mean?

329
00:30:51.726 --> 00:30:53.381
We're friends.

330
00:30:53.716 --> 00:30:54.827
Why do you ask?

331
00:31:08.350 --> 00:31:09.850
Taeko!

332
00:31:12.150 --> 00:31:14.424
I want to dye my hair again.

333
00:31:14.520 --> 00:31:17.527
There's no one in my house today.
can you dye it for me?

334
00:31:17.859 --> 00:31:18.995
Hey!

335
00:31:23.340 --> 00:31:24.389
I'm home.

336
00:31:28.090 --> 00:31:29.992
I heard from your mother.

337
00:31:30.302 --> 00:31:32.881
Tokyo schools won't allow it.

338
00:31:34.633 --> 00:31:37.744
But there's a school for hairdressers.
just not here.

339
00:31:37.990 --> 00:31:39.840
After you graduate from school.

340
00:31:42.520 --> 00:31:45.252
it's up to me to decide your future.

341
00:31:45.990 --> 00:31:47.180
Decide?

342
00:31:48.080 --> 00:31:49.690
What about my dreams?

343
00:31:52.409 --> 00:31:53.855
Come on. honey.

344
00:31:53.949 --> 00:31:56.170
She hasn't even graduated
high school.

345
00:31:57.269 --> 00:31:58.815
Listen to me.

346
00:31:59.135 --> 00:32:01.437
I'm not going to let you
to live on your own.

347
00:32:03.660 --> 00:32:05.535
When are you coming back this time?

348
00:32:05.630 --> 00:32:07.001
I will call you when I know.

349
00:32:23.325 --> 00:32:24.791
You are awful.

350
00:32:24.939 --> 00:32:26.189
You missed everything.

351
00:32:27.152 --> 00:32:31.197
I just like to modify things. you know?
I'm kind of inexperienced.

352
00:32:32.624 --> 00:32:36.266
It's a shame to mess with everything
and not actually use it.

353
00:32:36.979 --> 00:32:38.554
It gets frustrating.

354
00:32:38.649 --> 00:32:41.299
I'm always frustrated. Mamiya.

355
00:32:42.726 --> 00:32:44.367
Because it's a damn town.

356
00:32:45.590 --> 00:32:48.459
No karaoke. no arcade.
or video rental shops.

357
00:32:49.500 --> 00:32:51.253
There is no entertainment here.

358
00:32:51.919 --> 00:32:53.841
How come everyone doesn't get ill?

359
00:32:59.600 --> 00:33:00.920
But Mamiya. you know...

360
00:33:01.709 --> 00:33:04.135
It might be twisted to say this

361
00:33:04.230 --> 00:33:07.020
but that day my heart was beating so fast.

362
00:33:08.199 --> 00:33:10.219
I felt completely free.

363
00:33:18.389 --> 00:33:21.207
Your existence is twisted in itself.

364
00:34:02.599 --> 00:34:05.274
I told you not to get cheap beer.
you idiot!

365
00:34:05.370 --> 00:34:06.553
Dad...

366
00:34:07.819 --> 00:34:09.200
Buy it again.

367
00:34:12.109 --> 00:34:14.019
But it's already late.

368
00:34:14.839 --> 00:34:15.988
I don't have any money...

369
00:34:16.085 --> 00:34:18.015
Enough. just go!

370
00:36:33.589 --> 00:36:34.629
Nozaki!

371
00:36:36.120 --> 00:36:38.655
You don't have to force
yourself to come to school.

372
00:36:45.520 --> 00:36:47.559
Maybe it's not my business.

373
00:36:48.959 --> 00:36:50.071
But...

374
00:36:51.680 --> 00:36:53.516
is there anything I can do for you?

375
00:37:02.639 --> 00:37:04.130
Say something.

376
00:37:20.779 --> 00:37:21.807
Your voice?

377
00:37:25.180 --> 00:37:26.433
What's going on?

378
00:37:54.886 --> 00:37:56.002
That's disgusting.

379
00:38:43.879 --> 00:38:45.019
Where's Rumi?

380
00:38:46.129 --> 00:38:47.269
She ran away.

381
00:38:48.250 --> 00:38:49.464
Forget her.

382
00:38:49.599 --> 00:38:51.082
Whatever. she's disgusting.

383
00:38:51.800 --> 00:38:53.479
We'll do it on our own.

384
00:38:59.320 --> 00:39:00.540
Nozaki...

385
00:39:05.839 --> 00:39:08.178
You must be in a lot of pain. right?

386
00:39:08.819 --> 00:39:09.745
We...

387
00:39:09.839 --> 00:39:11.285
What are you talking about?

388
00:39:11.380 --> 00:39:13.182
It has nothing to do with us.

389
00:39:16.059 --> 00:39:17.601
Nosaki. come on...

390
00:39:20.278 --> 00:39:21.639
Are you going to kill yourself?

391
00:39:21.736 --> 00:39:24.357
Tachibana. what are you talking about?

392
00:39:25.070 --> 00:39:26.894
Look at her face.

393
00:39:27.247 --> 00:39:29.247
She already figured it out.

394
00:39:33.712 --> 00:39:35.011
Are you serious?

395
00:39:48.889 --> 00:39:50.684
You two. come over here.

396
00:40:08.779 --> 00:40:09.921
You know...

397
00:40:12.470 --> 00:40:15.869
I had thought about dying
every single day.

398
00:40:17.839 --> 00:40:20.944
But after I saw your mother burn to death

399
00:40:21.459 --> 00:40:24.328
I realized I didn't want to die.

400
00:40:26.600 --> 00:40:29.500
For the first time I felt that way!

401
00:40:30.740 --> 00:40:31.799
Because...

402
00:40:32.814 --> 00:40:35.117
they seemed to feel a lot of pain.

403
00:40:36.010 --> 00:40:38.230
You're getting on my nerves!

404
00:40:38.611 --> 00:40:41.753
Hurry up. I can't wait for you
to do something.

405
00:41:04.630 --> 00:41:06.049
What's this?

406
00:41:08.279 --> 00:41:10.887
Isn't it better if I don't touch it?

407
00:41:26.959 --> 00:41:28.045
You bitch!

408
00:41:28.139 --> 00:41:29.185
Nozaki!

409
00:41:52.299 --> 00:41:53.339
Dad...

410
00:42:10.489 --> 00:42:11.514
Hold on!

411
00:42:11.610 --> 00:42:14.474
Please wait! Listen to me!

412
00:42:14.570 --> 00:42:17.644
It was Kuga's fault!
Yes. it was Kuga!

413
00:42:17.700 --> 00:42:20.286
Did you see the burn on Kuga's hand?
That's the proof.

414
00:42:20.412 --> 00:42:23.457
It was Kuga who set your mother on fire!

415
00:42:23.581 --> 00:42:25.927
So we have nothing to do with it!

416
00:42:26.370 --> 00:42:27.378
Wait!

417
00:42:33.966 --> 00:42:35.843
Mom... mom...

418
00:43:22.890 --> 00:43:24.684
It's been snowing a lot lately.

419
00:43:24.779 --> 00:43:27.231
Yes. class might be cancelled tomorrow.

420
00:43:28.259 --> 00:43:30.634
I heard that Tachibana. Mishima and Katou

421
00:43:30.730 --> 00:43:32.474
haven't come home since yesterday.

422
00:43:32.569 --> 00:43:33.430
Really?

423
00:43:33.620 --> 00:43:35.459
Maybe the three ran away together.

424
00:43:36.189 --> 00:43:37.545
Maybe. It's possible.

425
00:43:38.459 --> 00:43:39.830
Look. a police car!

426
00:43:40.339 --> 00:43:41.517
Oh. really?

427
00:43:43.780 --> 00:43:45.974
- Police car?
- Wow. that's cool.

428
00:43:57.460 --> 00:43:59.675
There are policemen too.
They really came!

429
00:44:08.549 --> 00:44:10.857
Why are you all so scared?

430
00:44:13.839 --> 00:44:16.354
It must be because of the three
who didn't come home.

431
00:44:20.920 --> 00:44:21.749
Yeah...

432
00:44:24.279 --> 00:44:26.969
It's so cold. I'm going home.

433
00:44:59.320 --> 00:45:00.330
Nozaki?

434
00:45:05.899 --> 00:45:07.055
What's wrong?

435
00:45:12.600 --> 00:45:14.379
Are you skipping school today too?

436
00:45:15.260 --> 00:45:17.039
What do you want?

437
00:45:21.500 --> 00:45:23.114
What's your problem?

438
00:45:29.920 --> 00:45:31.003
Oh my God...

439
00:45:53.061 --> 00:45:54.338
Don't get close!

440
00:45:58.200 --> 00:45:59.374
Don't come over!

441
00:45:59.470 --> 00:46:00.490
It hurts!

442
00:46:20.350 --> 00:46:23.702
Don't come any closer!

443
00:47:08.796 --> 00:47:10.577
I wasn't the only one who did that...

444
00:47:27.259 --> 00:47:28.650
Got it.

445
00:47:33.469 --> 00:47:36.998
The school will be closed tomorrow
because of the snow.

446
00:47:38.369 --> 00:47:39.624
Excuse me.

447
00:47:42.350 --> 00:47:43.571
Yes.

448
00:47:44.749 --> 00:47:45.931
Yes!

449
00:47:55.149 --> 00:47:57.039
I tried calling her.

450
00:47:57.799 --> 00:48:00.054
but she doesn't want to get out of the bed.

451
00:48:01.689 --> 00:48:02.830
It's okay.

452
00:48:03.682 --> 00:48:05.278
I just came to visit her.

453
00:48:11.199 --> 00:48:14.159
Spring is just around the corner.

454
00:48:15.439 --> 00:48:19.229
It just takes a little more patience.

455
00:48:28.679 --> 00:48:31.551
When she graduates.

456
00:48:32.279 --> 00:48:34.541
I'm taking Haruka and Shoko

457
00:48:35.161 --> 00:48:37.496
back to Tokyo.

458
00:48:39.807 --> 00:48:41.087
Aiba...

459
00:48:41.786 --> 00:48:44.159
until the graduation ceremony.

460
00:48:44.520 --> 00:48:47.686
I'd like you to take care of her.

461
00:48:52.119 --> 00:48:53.457
Sure.

462
00:49:03.549 --> 00:49:05.274
We have to shovel the snow tomorrow.

463
00:49:05.370 --> 00:49:07.129
Rumi. can you help me?

464
00:49:07.260 --> 00:49:09.000
Yeah. sure.

465
00:49:09.419 --> 00:49:11.308
What's wrong?

466
00:49:12.319 --> 00:49:15.430
It's pretty rare. you staying
in the living room all this time.

467
00:49:15.530 --> 00:49:17.007
What's wrong?

468
00:49:18.110 --> 00:49:21.153
No... I just have a request.

469
00:49:21.250 --> 00:49:22.520
What's it?

470
00:49:24.989 --> 00:49:28.284
I would like to sleep with you tonight.

471
00:49:29.465 --> 00:49:31.930
What? Why?

472
00:49:32.539 --> 00:49:34.190
Nothing's happened.

473
00:49:35.750 --> 00:49:39.201
Rumi. you are still a spoiled brat.
aren't you?

474
00:49:40.890 --> 00:49:42.714
Okay. get the quilt.

475
00:49:42.942 --> 00:49:43.966
Okay.

476
00:50:11.023 --> 00:50:12.473
Hello?

477
00:50:12.973 --> 00:50:14.147
Hey Rumi!

478
00:50:15.100 --> 00:50:16.040
What's up?

479
00:50:16.330 --> 00:50:18.059
Don't what's up me! Idiot!

480
00:50:19.280 --> 00:50:20.835
Kuga's disappeared.

481
00:50:20.930 --> 00:50:22.989
It seems he hasn't come home.

482
00:50:24.413 --> 00:50:27.912
Those three girls went missing.
and now it's him.

483
00:50:28.360 --> 00:50:30.159
We can be sure now.

484
00:50:31.439 --> 00:50:32.658
It's Nozaki.

485
00:50:33.280 --> 00:50:35.530
Nosaka attacked those girls from the back.

486
00:50:36.480 --> 00:50:38.919
A... Attacked from behind?

487
00:50:39.519 --> 00:50:42.697
Maybe the next one is you.
the mastermind.

488
00:50:42.817 --> 00:50:44.896
Don't talk nonsense!

489
00:50:45.479 --> 00:50:48.240
We have to make a move
before she comes for us.

490
00:50:48.639 --> 00:50:50.776
We are going to take
care of her tomorrow.

491
00:50:51.679 --> 00:50:53.302
Well. just wait and see.

492
00:51:05.559 --> 00:51:07.849
Will you be all right on your own?

493
00:51:11.040 --> 00:51:12.589
Be careful.

494
00:51:24.116 --> 00:51:25.428
She left!

495
00:51:56.820 --> 00:51:59.569
I didn't think you'd miss her
at this distance.

496
00:52:00.329 --> 00:52:03.107
Do you get nervous when
the target is a person?

497
00:52:03.470 --> 00:52:04.600
Shut up!

498
00:52:13.629 --> 00:52:15.899
She ran away so fast.

499
00:52:16.170 --> 00:52:18.870
But don't you think it
feels more like a hunt now?

500
00:52:20.608 --> 00:52:23.693
You're not going to kill anyone
with a toy gun. are you?

501
00:52:25.979 --> 00:52:27.593
What about if we split up?

502
00:52:27.689 --> 00:52:30.349
I'm starting to get excited. Mamiya.

503
00:52:42.480 --> 00:52:44.800
In this shitty place. with nothing...

504
00:52:45.199 --> 00:52:47.826
your existence is like poison.

505
00:52:48.799 --> 00:52:52.600
Because you are too beautiful.

506
00:52:56.880 --> 00:52:59.309
Nozaki!

507
00:53:00.479 --> 00:53:02.889
I threatened your father
with this crossbow.

508
00:53:03.680 --> 00:53:06.139
I was the one who
set your house on fire.

509
00:53:08.939 --> 00:53:12.589
Don't you want to
avenge your family?

510
00:53:30.720 --> 00:53:31.920
Nozaki.

511
00:53:32.429 --> 00:53:35.629
I never thought
I could see you so close.

512
00:53:47.500 --> 00:53:49.319
You damn bitch girl!

513
00:54:16.969 --> 00:54:18.440
Get out of the way.

514
00:54:19.579 --> 00:54:21.070
You are getting in the way. asshole.

515
00:54:32.160 --> 00:54:33.200
Ikegawa…

516
00:54:40.350 --> 00:54:41.793
Nozaki.

517
00:54:42.929 --> 00:54:44.546
I love you.

518
00:54:44.886 --> 00:54:46.431
I've liked you for a long time...

519
00:54:47.390 --> 00:54:49.264
in love with you.

520
00:54:49.599 --> 00:54:52.384
You're out of your mind!

521
00:55:13.130 --> 00:55:15.125
Time out! Time out!

522
00:55:18.859 --> 00:55:21.772
I said. time out. bitch!

523
00:56:18.300 --> 00:56:19.905
Ms. Minami.

524
00:56:19.999 --> 00:56:23.145
My son. Hidetoshi
has not returned home yet.

525
00:56:23.240 --> 00:56:25.960
Mrs. Kuga. I'm sorry. but we don't...

526
00:56:26.092 --> 00:56:27.362
Why. principal...

527
00:56:27.458 --> 00:56:30.203
didn't three students
from the same class go home?

528
00:56:30.300 --> 00:56:32.459
Ms. Minami. you are their
homeroom teacher. right?

529
00:56:32.620 --> 00:56:34.886
Don't you have any ideas?

530
00:56:38.436 --> 00:56:39.603
What?

531
00:56:40.680 --> 00:56:42.209
What are you laughing at?

532
00:56:43.129 --> 00:56:45.340
This woman is insane.

533
00:56:47.648 --> 00:56:49.834
You are the insane one here.

534
00:56:52.555 --> 00:56:54.241
Ah. my bad.

535
00:56:54.338 --> 00:56:56.123
I said it out loud.

536
00:57:04.890 --> 00:57:06.074
Stop it!

537
00:57:06.170 --> 00:57:07.719
Principal. stop it.

538
00:57:23.356 --> 00:57:27.234
<i>A cold wave has been hitting the
Japanese archipelago since Saturday...</i>

539
00:57:27.400 --> 00:57:30.863
<i>is causing heavy snowfalls
and snowstorms...</i>

540
00:57:30.987 --> 00:57:32.794
You're late.

541
00:57:32.906 --> 00:57:34.532
I was worried.

542
00:57:36.284 --> 00:57:38.536
What... happened?

543
00:57:49.500 --> 00:57:51.494
You must be cold.

544
00:57:52.139 --> 00:57:53.841
Go take a shower.

545
00:58:27.713 --> 00:58:29.401
Excuse me. is anyone home?

546
00:58:33.320 --> 00:58:34.680
Nozaki?

547
00:59:39.239 --> 00:59:41.315
I thought...

548
00:59:42.026 --> 00:59:44.616
I would never see you again.

549
00:59:51.679 --> 00:59:53.501
I have always wanted to see you.

550
00:59:58.920 --> 01:00:00.558
I wanted to see you.

551
01:00:16.349 --> 01:00:17.359
Nozaki?

552
01:00:50.969 --> 01:00:54.062
I will protect you.

553
01:01:12.619 --> 01:01:13.907
Thank you...

554
01:02:27.660 --> 01:02:30.050
When all this snow is gone.

555
01:02:34.039 --> 01:02:36.379
And after you graduate.

556
01:02:38.879 --> 01:02:42.509
Let's go back to grandpa's house in Tokyo.

557
01:02:46.059 --> 01:02:49.111
And we're moving
Shoko to another hospital too.

558
01:02:50.379 --> 01:02:52.830
Let's get out of here.

559
01:02:56.000 --> 01:02:57.819
Grandpa. I'm sorry.

560
01:03:05.639 --> 01:03:06.943
Shouko...

561
01:03:07.381 --> 01:03:09.166
I'm sorry.

562
01:03:15.820 --> 01:03:19.230
Haruka. do you want to stay here?

563
01:03:28.200 --> 01:03:33.330
Shouko's transfer procedure
is already in process.

564
01:03:35.574 --> 01:03:36.691
But...

565
01:03:41.389 --> 01:03:42.877
It's okay.

566
01:03:45.759 --> 01:03:47.702
Let's take it easy.

567
01:03:55.041 --> 01:03:56.425
Tokyo?

568
01:03:56.580 --> 01:03:58.250
Are you going to Tokyo?

569
01:03:58.800 --> 01:04:00.959
What about the school
you were planning to go to?

570
01:04:02.649 --> 01:04:04.539
I won't go to the local
high school in this town.

571
01:04:06.040 --> 01:04:09.129
I'll be going to school at night
and working in Tokyo.

572
01:04:13.279 --> 01:04:15.376
There is someone
I want to live with there.

573
01:04:18.239 --> 01:04:19.420
Because she...

574
01:04:25.960 --> 01:04:28.452
she has nobody to count on.

575
01:05:59.290 --> 01:06:01.530
Rumi. it's time for breakfast.

576
01:06:01.980 --> 01:06:03.089
I don't want it.

577
01:06:04.319 --> 01:06:05.904
Tell me if you want to eat.

578
01:06:06.213 --> 01:06:08.842
I will make it for you anytime.

579
01:06:17.240 --> 01:06:18.949
I want to kill her.

580
01:06:19.918 --> 01:06:21.369
What?

581
01:06:24.499 --> 01:06:26.343
I want her dead.

582
01:06:28.178 --> 01:06:29.342
Hey Rumi.

583
01:06:30.119 --> 01:06:32.363
Did you just say "I want to kill her"?

584
01:06:32.939 --> 01:06:34.515
I heard that too.

585
01:06:35.137 --> 01:06:36.395
She certainly said.

586
01:06:36.450 --> 01:06:40.140
I heard it too. "I want to kill her".

587
01:06:41.231 --> 01:06:43.153
Even you have no guts.

588
01:06:43.250 --> 01:06:45.255
So stop talking nonsense!

589
01:06:47.989 --> 01:06:49.257
I'll do it.

590
01:06:50.673 --> 01:06:52.162
I can do it.

591
01:06:54.125 --> 01:06:55.656
I'm gonna kill her.

592
01:06:56.960 --> 01:06:59.294
I will pour kerosene over her house.

593
01:06:59.389 --> 01:07:01.299
And make it look like a fire.

594
01:07:01.578 --> 01:07:03.588
Burn her to death.

595
01:07:03.960 --> 01:07:07.130
Why are you getting so excited. idiot!

596
01:07:32.839 --> 01:07:36.159
Hey you. how many phone
calls are you going to make?

597
01:07:36.719 --> 01:07:38.088
Taeko.

598
01:07:38.897 --> 01:07:41.268
I'm going to be killed.

599
01:07:41.364 --> 01:07:43.554
I'm going to be killed by her.

600
01:07:45.456 --> 01:07:46.955
You reap what you sow. right?

601
01:07:47.148 --> 01:07:48.809
Taeko!

602
01:07:48.954 --> 01:07:49.704
I'm hanging up.

603
01:07:49.799 --> 01:07:51.565
Hang on. wait! wait!

604
01:07:51.660 --> 01:07:52.950
What's it now?

605
01:07:54.160 --> 01:07:56.955
Tachibana and the other two.
I found them lying dead on the back hill.

606
01:07:57.052 --> 01:07:59.199
They were killed.

607
01:07:59.509 --> 01:08:00.435
Liar!

608
01:08:00.529 --> 01:08:03.479
I told the truth. please believe me.

609
01:08:03.900 --> 01:08:09.890
Maybe you are going to get killed as well.
and I will be the next one.

610
01:08:10.758 --> 01:08:13.894
Have I done anything that
would make her want to kill me?

611
01:08:13.990 --> 01:08:15.894
It's your fault!

612
01:08:16.273 --> 01:08:17.452
What?

613
01:08:18.486 --> 01:08:19.926
Taeko.

614
01:08:20.351 --> 01:08:22.429
Don't you hate her?

615
01:08:23.460 --> 01:08:26.690
Because Nozaki... stole Aiba from you.

616
01:08:27.909 --> 01:08:29.464
You got the wrong idea.

617
01:08:29.559 --> 01:08:31.544
There's no way I could ever
like that guy!

618
01:08:31.640 --> 01:08:33.305
Then why?

619
01:08:33.399 --> 01:08:37.492
Why did you let everyone
bully her like that?

620
01:08:40.239 --> 01:08:41.290
Myo-chan...

621
01:08:41.917 --> 01:08:43.555
don't say...

622
01:08:44.849 --> 01:08:46.275
No way!

623
01:08:46.369 --> 01:08:48.802
Don't talk to me like you know me.

624
01:08:49.280 --> 01:08:50.590
Die.

625
01:09:33.569 --> 01:09:35.363
Hey. are you really going to do it?

626
01:09:35.459 --> 01:09:37.808
Seriously. this is so funny.

627
01:09:38.410 --> 01:09:39.824
Hey Rumi.

628
01:09:39.934 --> 01:09:43.150
If you do it halfway.
you are going to have it rough.

629
01:09:44.626 --> 01:09:47.213
Those who are afraid
should just go back home.

630
01:09:49.459 --> 01:09:51.607
Before you regret it.

631
01:09:53.300 --> 01:09:54.885
What are you talking about?

632
01:09:54.980 --> 01:09:56.978
You've got a lot of guts. huh.

633
01:09:58.019 --> 01:10:00.170
You're pretty brave. aren't you?

634
01:10:01.500 --> 01:10:04.856
If that's the case.
we'll also cooperate fully.

635
01:10:05.157 --> 01:10:06.550
- Right?
- Yeah.

636
01:10:07.920 --> 01:10:09.108
But in return...

637
01:10:09.831 --> 01:10:12.438
If the mastermind. that's you. backs out.

638
01:10:12.535 --> 01:10:14.205
I'll seriously kill you.

639
01:10:14.780 --> 01:10:16.204
What was that?

640
01:10:16.299 --> 01:10:18.284
It's a test of courage for her.

641
01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:20.613
Taeko's going too. right?

642
01:10:23.250 --> 01:10:24.970
That's so boring.

643
01:10:25.510 --> 01:10:26.949
I'm going home.

644
01:10:30.551 --> 01:10:31.781
Taeko.

645
01:10:31.875 --> 01:10:33.486
just wait and see!

646
01:10:33.710 --> 01:10:35.320
Good luck.

647
01:11:28.672 --> 01:11:32.051
♪ The path ♪
<i>(hitori de)</i>

648
01:11:32.052 --> 01:11:34.693
♪ that I walked alone ♪
<i>(aruku)</i>

649
01:11:34.694 --> 01:11:39.595
♪ turned the journey ♪
<i>(michi nori ga)</i>

650
01:11:40.495 --> 01:11:46.343
♪ into something sad ♪
<i>(sabishi monoda to)</i>

651
01:11:46.743 --> 01:11:52.085
♪ When I felt this ♪
<i>(kanjita toki)</i>

652
01:11:52.086 --> 01:11:57.412
♪ The living beings ♪
<i>(nukumori o motsu)</i>

653
01:11:58.146 --> 01:12:03.106
♪ that have warmth ♪
<i>(ikimono tachi wa)</i>

654
01:12:03.616 --> 01:12:09.374
♪ began to hold hands ♪
<i>(tagaini te o)</i>

655
01:12:09.375 --> 01:12:14.028
♪ began to hold hands ♪
<i>(tori hajimeru)</i>

656
01:12:19.619 --> 01:12:20.954
Excuse me.

657
01:12:22.130 --> 01:12:23.731
Is anybody here?

658
01:13:27.820 --> 01:13:29.220
Ah. thank you.

659
01:13:32.961 --> 01:13:34.325
I'm sorry. grandpa.

660
01:13:34.429 --> 01:13:36.237
Can you go back first?

661
01:13:40.419 --> 01:13:42.609
Yeah. well. be careful.

662
01:14:07.203 --> 01:14:08.414
This...

663
01:14:08.902 --> 01:14:10.595
I have to give it back.

664
01:14:10.756 --> 01:14:12.519
I've been thinking about it.

665
01:14:13.645 --> 01:14:15.785
Have you been listening to this?

666
01:14:16.276 --> 01:14:18.700
It feels like a long time ago.

667
01:14:25.720 --> 01:14:27.720
You and me...

668
01:14:28.885 --> 01:14:31.039
It's been a long time since
we've been like this.

669
01:14:32.844 --> 01:14:35.342
Taeko. haven't you been sleeping?

670
01:14:36.337 --> 01:14:38.265
What kind of question is that?

671
01:14:41.660 --> 01:14:44.202
Why are you so scared?

672
01:14:45.908 --> 01:14:47.454
Because...

673
01:14:49.227 --> 01:14:51.759
Don't you think you're acting weird?

674
01:14:55.819 --> 01:14:57.838
Could it be that I'm weird?

675
01:15:00.960 --> 01:15:03.999
I'm the one who caused the death
of your family. and yet...

676
01:15:06.989 --> 01:15:08.919
Maybe it's true.

677
01:15:17.291 --> 01:15:18.484
I...

678
01:15:24.180 --> 01:15:25.714
What should I...

679
01:15:26.116 --> 01:15:28.086
say to you?

680
01:15:36.010 --> 01:15:37.527
I'm...

681
01:15:43.950 --> 01:15:45.480
I'm not the kind of person...

682
01:15:45.543 --> 01:15:47.580
you need to apologize to.

683
01:15:51.705 --> 01:15:52.895
I'm not.

684
01:15:56.377 --> 01:15:57.860
You fool.

685
01:16:06.529 --> 01:16:09.311
Remember when I first came to school?

686
01:16:10.049 --> 01:16:13.503
It was you Taeko. the first person
who spoke to me.

687
01:16:15.795 --> 01:16:17.781
<i>She wanted to go to Tokyo...</i>

688
01:16:18.149 --> 01:16:20.718
<i>She told me she had a dream
of becoming a hairdresser there.</i>

689
01:16:20.813 --> 01:16:22.606
Nozaki. do you have a minute?

690
01:16:23.208 --> 01:16:25.288
<i>However...</i>

691
01:16:26.809 --> 01:16:29.860
<i>I was hurting her.</i>

692
01:16:31.319 --> 01:16:33.009
It's not like that!

693
01:16:34.892 --> 01:16:38.328
I was never jealous of you and Aiba.

694
01:16:38.769 --> 01:16:40.134
I was...

695
01:16:44.346 --> 01:16:45.492
What?

696
01:16:56.645 --> 01:16:58.256
It’s nothing.

697
01:17:15.440 --> 01:17:17.549
Nozaki. do you have a minute?

698
01:17:34.577 --> 01:17:37.925
<i>I just couldn't forgive you for
leaving me because of that guy.</i>

699
01:17:38.919 --> 01:17:41.385
<i>I wanted her to look only at me.</i>

700
01:17:51.619 --> 01:17:54.683
How did we end up in this situation?

701
01:18:11.400 --> 01:18:13.473
It's been nice talking to you.

702
01:18:21.960 --> 01:18:23.590
Taeko!

703
01:18:30.073 --> 01:18:32.504
Live with your head held high.

704
01:18:43.320 --> 01:18:44.698
Nozaki!

705
01:18:47.551 --> 01:18:49.071
Please...

706
01:18:50.556 --> 01:18:52.787
Forgive me!

707
01:19:41.299 --> 01:19:42.636
Rumi!

708
01:19:44.850 --> 01:19:46.809
You're a real pain in the ass.

709
01:19:58.700 --> 01:20:00.564
You are screaming!

710
01:20:02.229 --> 01:20:04.230
You are screaming! You are screaming!

711
01:20:04.439 --> 01:20:06.904
The cool Taeko. she screamed!

712
01:20:08.670 --> 01:20:12.055
How pathetic... Are you stupid or what?

713
01:20:12.150 --> 01:20:14.472
Ela gritou de dor!

714
01:20:14.568 --> 01:20:16.708
You crazy bitch!

715
01:20:31.784 --> 01:20:33.316
Ta... Taeko!

716
01:20:39.736 --> 01:20:41.052
Taeko!

717
01:20:43.541 --> 01:20:46.560
Does it hurt? Does it hurt?

718
01:20:47.111 --> 01:20:48.767
Does it hurt? Does it hurt?

719
01:21:05.309 --> 01:21:08.631
Because of something stupid you did.

720
01:21:08.966 --> 01:21:11.410
Why don't you just
go to hell. stupid bitch?

721
01:21:12.099 --> 01:21:14.106
I don't understand what
you're talking about.

722
01:21:14.362 --> 01:21:15.969
It's fucking annoying.

723
01:21:16.372 --> 01:21:18.346
Everyone. without exception. clings to me

724
01:21:18.346 --> 01:21:20.888
gets sick and goes crazy
on their own.

725
01:21:21.167 --> 01:21:23.039
I'm sick of you all!

726
01:21:23.320 --> 01:21:25.650
Why did you go to her house?

727
01:21:25.897 --> 01:21:28.597
You have always looked at
me with your lewd eyes.

728
01:21:28.809 --> 01:21:31.605
Did you think if you killed her.
you will get my attention?

729
01:21:31.699 --> 01:21:33.365
I did it for you Taeko...

730
01:21:35.091 --> 01:21:36.044
I did it for you...

731
01:21:36.140 --> 01:21:37.270
Disgusting!

732
01:21:37.367 --> 01:21:37.792
Taeko...

733
01:21:37.792 --> 01:21:39.428
You fucking disgusting murderer!

734
01:21:39.428 --> 01:21:41.818
I did it for you Taeko!

735
01:22:20.370 --> 01:22:22.342
The fearless Taeko.

736
01:22:23.149 --> 01:22:24.439
I liked her.

737
01:22:25.749 --> 01:22:26.885
Now...

738
01:22:27.974 --> 01:22:30.838
it just looks like an old. dirty rag.

739
01:22:54.729 --> 01:22:56.550
With these hands...

740
01:22:57.865 --> 01:22:59.445
how am I going to...

741
01:23:00.740 --> 01:23:03.006
hold scissors?

742
01:23:13.783 --> 01:23:14.776
Yes.

743
01:23:17.497 --> 01:23:18.554
Haruka!

744
01:23:19.285 --> 01:23:21.644
Aiba is calling.

745
01:23:28.300 --> 01:23:29.480
Hello!

746
01:23:29.953 --> 01:23:31.265
You see...

747
01:23:31.434 --> 01:23:33.410
I've heard from your grandpa.

748
01:23:33.569 --> 01:23:36.169
You are going back to
Tokyo after you graduate.

749
01:23:37.312 --> 01:23:38.471
Yeah.

750
01:23:39.386 --> 01:23:40.105
But...

751
01:23:40.200 --> 01:23:41.283
I know.

752
01:23:41.791 --> 01:23:44.747
I just convinced my granny about that.

753
01:23:45.459 --> 01:23:47.696
I'm not going to school from here.

754
01:23:48.036 --> 01:23:51.259
I'm going to Tokyo with you.

755
01:23:52.267 --> 01:23:53.138
What?

756
01:23:53.565 --> 01:23:56.669
I will find a place and work.

757
01:23:57.411 --> 01:23:59.587
You don't have to worry about anything.

758
01:24:00.784 --> 01:24:01.953
But...

759
01:24:02.749 --> 01:24:04.946
I probably won't be able to go.

760
01:24:06.437 --> 01:24:07.507
Why?

761
01:24:09.381 --> 01:24:11.770
You'll understand when
spring arrives.

762
01:24:13.520 --> 01:24:15.183
So. Aiba...

763
01:24:15.279 --> 01:24:16.696
Why don't you go to school here?

764
01:24:16.792 --> 01:24:18.618
Didn't you promise me?

765
01:24:23.363 --> 01:24:25.237
I said I would protect you.

766
01:24:25.333 --> 01:24:26.803
You promised me...

767
01:24:27.848 --> 01:24:29.849
Didn't you promise?

768
01:24:41.017 --> 01:24:42.739
It's not because of me.

769
01:24:44.585 --> 01:24:47.043
You're going to choose your family.
aren't you?

770
01:25:17.100 --> 01:25:18.138
Grandpa.

771
01:25:18.138 --> 01:25:20.440
You never ask me anything.

772
01:25:22.437 --> 01:25:23.967
Whenever you're ready.

773
01:25:24.062 --> 01:25:26.203
You can talk to me.

774
01:25:27.694 --> 01:25:29.099
All right?

775
01:25:35.375 --> 01:25:37.484
It's almost done. right?

776
01:25:45.221 --> 01:25:46.601
Granny?

777
01:25:47.889 --> 01:25:48.946
Granny?

778
01:25:52.049 --> 01:25:53.255
Granny?

779
01:25:53.823 --> 01:25:56.823
What's wrong? Are you still sitting here?

780
01:25:57.932 --> 01:26:00.932
If you sleep here.
you will catch a cold.

781
01:26:02.648 --> 01:26:04.214
Mitsuru...

782
01:26:06.316 --> 01:26:07.417
Granny...

783
01:26:08.529 --> 01:26:11.767
has always believed in you. but...

784
01:26:12.412 --> 01:26:13.921
You've...

785
01:26:14.509 --> 01:26:16.796
always been like this...

786
01:26:17.149 --> 01:26:20.398
Did you stab your dad?

787
01:26:22.739 --> 01:26:24.279
That was different.

788
01:26:28.199 --> 01:26:32.509
Because dad was hitting mom
every single day.

789
01:26:33.980 --> 01:26:36.176
I just tried to make him stop.

790
01:26:38.981 --> 01:26:40.244
Then what about your mother?

791
01:26:40.340 --> 01:26:41.544
No. no...

792
01:26:44.620 --> 01:26:48.005
When I stabbed Dad in the back
with a cutter...

793
01:26:49.009 --> 01:26:52.279
there's no one left to hit mom...

794
01:26:54.421 --> 01:26:56.047
But she still wanted someone to beat her.

795
01:26:56.548 --> 01:26:59.015
wanted someone to beat her.

796
01:27:00.855 --> 01:27:03.940
So I did it for her.

797
01:27:07.299 --> 01:27:09.722
Let's stop talking about the past.

798
01:27:19.859 --> 01:27:21.651
I'm sorry. Granny.

799
01:27:27.970 --> 01:27:30.469
I love you very much. Grandma.

800
01:27:32.451 --> 01:27:35.108
I loved mom and dad too.

801
01:27:38.637 --> 01:27:40.865
When it comes to someone I love.

802
01:27:40.962 --> 01:27:42.477
I'm a disaster.

803
01:27:44.023 --> 01:27:45.426
I get angry...

804
01:27:46.038 --> 01:27:48.189
and end up losing control.

805
01:28:05.770 --> 01:28:09.024
When I asked Nozaki to live with me

806
01:28:09.119 --> 01:28:11.944
she said she wanted to be with her family.

807
01:28:12.426 --> 01:28:14.914
Actually. she wants to live with me.

808
01:28:40.480 --> 01:28:42.920
Tomorrow I'm going to see her grandpa.

809
01:28:43.093 --> 01:28:44.725
I'll ask him directly.

810
01:28:47.469 --> 01:28:49.595
Rumi! What happened?

811
01:28:49.690 --> 01:28:51.208
Leave me alone!

812
01:28:51.409 --> 01:28:52.644
I'm coming in. okay?

813
01:28:52.739 --> 01:28:55.037
Don’t come in. you filthy old hag!

814
01:28:58.407 --> 01:29:00.610
Don't be so nice to me.

815
01:29:02.320 --> 01:29:04.174
Don't be kind...

816
01:29:12.358 --> 01:29:14.461
No matter what happens...

817
01:29:14.677 --> 01:29:17.777
mommy is on your side.

818
01:29:30.382 --> 01:29:31.877
I have to do it.

819
01:29:46.787 --> 01:29:47.783
Tomorrow.

820
01:29:47.880 --> 01:29:49.657
are you going to visit your sister?

821
01:29:50.260 --> 01:29:51.576
Yeah.

822
01:29:51.910 --> 01:29:53.976
It looks like the snow will weaken too.

823
01:29:56.981 --> 01:29:58.182
That's right.

824
01:30:09.090 --> 01:30:12.120
I heard that Taeko-chan has also
been out of contact since yesterday.

825
01:30:12.221 --> 01:30:15.781
My daughter hasn't returned
home for several days either.

826
01:30:16.017 --> 01:30:18.145
<i>If something happened
with my daughter. I...</i>

827
01:30:19.286 --> 01:30:20.326
Ms. Minami.

828
01:30:21.019 --> 01:30:22.100
That woman...

829
01:30:22.299 --> 01:30:23.313
It's her fault.

830
01:30:23.410 --> 01:30:25.275
Ms. Kuga. please calm down.

831
01:30:25.370 --> 01:30:28.044
Even though several of your own
students are missing..

832
01:30:28.139 --> 01:30:29.665
You seem quite calm. don't you?

833
01:30:29.714 --> 01:30:31.800
I heard from my daughter...

834
01:30:31.925 --> 01:30:35.333
that Mr. Minami saw
Taeko-chan as a 'friend'

835
01:30:35.430 --> 01:30:37.664
This woman is insane.

836
01:30:40.549 --> 01:30:43.465
Because of this. if I'm crazy

837
01:30:44.520 --> 01:30:47.547
then I wouldn't be fit to be
a teacher. right?

838
01:30:52.509 --> 01:30:53.852
Mr. Tachibana!

839
01:30:54.280 --> 01:30:55.630
I heard...

840
01:30:55.725 --> 01:30:58.550
that you’re from
Otsuma Junior High School.

841
01:30:59.490 --> 01:31:02.489
And they said you were
bullied back then.

842
01:31:04.209 --> 01:31:05.635
I get it.

843
01:31:06.812 --> 01:31:09.010
I get sick looking at you.

844
01:31:11.379 --> 01:31:14.557
You went crazy because
of the bullying. didn’t you?

845
01:31:15.967 --> 01:31:19.058
I bet our kids were scared too. huh?

846
01:31:20.256 --> 01:31:21.383
Actually...

847
01:31:21.478 --> 01:31:24.676
I think you killed a student. didn't you?

848
01:31:26.296 --> 01:31:27.115
That's terrible!

849
01:31:28.709 --> 01:31:31.458
You all know it too. don’t you?

850
01:31:32.249 --> 01:31:36.215
Our children are not the type to
let others manipulate them.

851
01:31:36.658 --> 01:31:39.167
They're the kind who do something.

852
01:31:42.079 --> 01:31:44.243
Do you want to puke again?
You puke girl!

853
01:31:44.339 --> 01:31:45.944
Seriously. just die.

854
01:31:46.040 --> 01:31:47.635
Annoying. isn't it?

855
01:31:47.737 --> 01:31:49.434
Yeah. that's so annoying.

856
01:31:57.239 --> 01:31:58.390
No!

857
01:31:58.509 --> 01:32:00.387
I'm a teacher!

858
01:32:01.050 --> 01:32:04.926
To erase that hateful past
in which I was bullied...

859
01:32:05.022 --> 01:32:08.218
I wanted to relive my middle
school years all over again.

860
01:32:08.372 --> 01:32:11.513
Even if it was as a teacher.
I wanted to go back to school

861
01:32:11.608 --> 01:32:13.724
and make friends!

862
01:32:15.179 --> 01:32:17.132
I just wanted to graduate
at Otsuma School...

863
01:32:17.559 --> 01:32:19.489
I just wanted to graduate
at Otsuma School!

864
01:32:19.799 --> 01:32:21.661
That was it!

865
01:32:30.720 --> 01:32:32.590
I can't believe she threw up!

866
01:32:32.769 --> 01:32:33.980
It's disgusting.

867
01:32:42.159 --> 01:32:44.849
Miss! Miss!

868
01:32:45.717 --> 01:32:48.287
Ms. Minami!

869
01:32:49.019 --> 01:32:50.039
Miss!

870
01:33:30.575 --> 01:33:33.349
What is the room number for Ms. Nozaki?

871
01:33:47.346 --> 01:33:48.835
Gross!

872
01:33:49.196 --> 01:33:50.667
What are you doing here?

873
01:33:53.330 --> 01:33:55.381
Don't come near me. you murderer!

874
01:33:58.510 --> 01:34:01.686
You don't want your sister
to be burned twice. do you?

875
01:34:03.050 --> 01:34:04.475
If it gets burned any more...

876
01:34:05.229 --> 01:34:08.054
You won't be able to eat any more.

877
01:34:09.170 --> 01:34:12.269
Your precious barbecue.

878
01:34:16.781 --> 01:34:19.103
Even if she's alive. it's useless.

879
01:34:20.025 --> 01:34:22.285
I will finish her off for you.

880
01:34:40.290 --> 01:34:44.115
Are you going to kill someone
in front of your sister?

881
01:35:05.749 --> 01:35:07.758
I heard you were here.

882
01:35:14.998 --> 01:35:16.608
I just came to see you.

883
01:35:19.499 --> 01:35:20.610
Nozaki!

884
01:35:21.243 --> 01:35:22.323
Your grandpa.

885
01:35:22.423 --> 01:35:24.984
Your grandpa. he called an ambulance.

886
01:35:25.080 --> 01:35:27.629
While you were here.
someone attacked him.

887
01:35:28.100 --> 01:35:29.834
Nozaki. it will be okay.

888
01:35:29.929 --> 01:35:31.005
Don't worry.

889
01:35:31.151 --> 01:35:32.264
Coming through!

890
01:35:32.781 --> 01:35:34.384
- Grandpa...
- Coming through!

891
01:35:34.737 --> 01:35:35.945
Grandpa!

892
01:36:03.560 --> 01:36:04.520
Aiba!

893
01:36:13.458 --> 01:36:14.636
Aiba!

894
01:36:15.075 --> 01:36:16.667
Show me your hands.

895
01:36:17.461 --> 01:36:18.742
Why?

896
01:36:19.022 --> 01:36:20.709
Let me see your hands.

897
01:36:21.899 --> 01:36:23.104
Let me see your hands!

898
01:36:23.856 --> 01:36:25.413
Let me see them!

899
01:36:35.609 --> 01:36:36.759
It's from yesterday.

900
01:36:36.854 --> 01:36:39.937
I got the scar when I was trying
to convince my grandma...

901
01:36:44.877 --> 01:36:45.933
But...

902
01:36:46.215 --> 01:36:48.215
I did it for us.

903
01:36:52.904 --> 01:36:54.687
Even your grandfather...

904
01:36:54.853 --> 01:36:56.854
I want him to understand me well.

905
01:37:02.500 --> 01:37:04.080
Because we...

906
01:37:05.231 --> 01:37:06.961
have to live together.

907
01:37:09.529 --> 01:37:10.843
Right?

908
01:37:16.583 --> 01:37:17.704
Nozaki...

909
01:37:25.820 --> 01:37:27.540
Ah. damn it.

910
01:37:30.769 --> 01:37:32.728
If it weren't for you...

911
01:37:34.879 --> 01:37:36.763
That's why you started the fire?

912
01:37:45.657 --> 01:37:47.240
<i>Eh. it smells bad.</i>

913
01:37:53.265 --> 01:37:55.360
What are you guys doing?!

914
01:38:00.195 --> 01:38:01.535
Hey old lady.

915
01:38:02.177 --> 01:38:04.383
I'd like you to keep this a secret.

916
01:38:04.717 --> 01:38:06.193
We are leaving today

917
01:38:06.997 --> 01:38:08.752
but if you tell anyone...

918
01:38:09.474 --> 01:38:11.294
We'll be coming back. you know?

919
01:38:11.488 --> 01:38:12.894
Go ahead. Kuga.

920
01:38:13.732 --> 01:38:16.556
I kinda want to see someone burn to death.

921
01:38:17.216 --> 01:38:18.788
What are you saying. idiot!

922
01:38:24.274 --> 01:38:25.756
Mom?

923
01:38:29.970 --> 01:38:31.975
It was a really bad smell.

924
01:38:32.481 --> 01:38:33.713
from your mother when she burned up.

925
01:38:33.809 --> 01:38:34.679
Don't!

926
01:38:35.036 --> 01:38:36.054
Kanako!

927
01:38:37.979 --> 01:38:39.029
Don't...

928
01:38:39.126 --> 01:38:40.126
Dad!

929
01:38:45.047 --> 01:38:46.173
Don't do it!

930
01:38:48.669 --> 01:38:49.499
Stop it!

931
01:38:49.868 --> 01:38:51.093
What are you doing?

932
01:38:52.780 --> 01:38:54.486
What are you going to do?
What are you going to do?!

933
01:38:54.486 --> 01:38:54.916
Shut up!

934
01:38:55.013 --> 01:38:56.007
Don't!

935
01:38:57.150 --> 01:38:58.087
Hey. Rumi!

936
01:39:00.022 --> 01:39:00.872
Hey...

937
01:39:02.119 --> 01:39:04.950
Stop... stop please!

938
01:39:14.113 --> 01:39:15.406
Stop...

939
01:39:18.118 --> 01:39:19.326
Stop...

940
01:39:19.952 --> 01:39:21.079
Stop...

941
01:39:21.204 --> 01:39:22.831
Stop!

942
01:39:29.620 --> 01:39:30.670
Nozaki!

943
01:40:58.649 --> 01:40:59.869
You're safe now.

944
01:41:09.221 --> 01:41:10.280
It was not like what you think.

945
01:41:11.674 --> 01:41:13.294
Don't get me wrong. Nozaki

946
01:41:18.409 --> 01:41:19.441
That day...

947
01:41:19.756 --> 01:41:22.106
your father was covering
and protecting Shouko.

948
01:41:22.475 --> 01:41:24.426
I thought it was very impressive.

949
01:41:25.370 --> 01:41:28.290
I thought he was a real example of a father
who loves his child.

950
01:41:29.479 --> 01:41:31.285
The bravery of such a father...

951
01:41:31.935 --> 01:41:34.683
I just thought I'd show it to you
at some point.

952
01:42:07.340 --> 01:42:09.886
I can't believe you're trying to kill me.

953
01:42:25.199 --> 01:42:27.250
I said I would protect you. didn't I?

954
01:42:33.629 --> 01:42:36.700
I said I'd protect you. didn't I?!

955
01:42:38.569 --> 01:42:39.899
Nozaki!

956
01:42:45.379 --> 01:42:47.486
Why don't you understand?

957
01:42:49.390 --> 01:42:51.759
Your sister won't last very long.

958
01:42:54.422 --> 01:42:56.459
And Grandpa's not gonna make it.

959
01:42:59.713 --> 01:43:02.137
The only person you can
count on is me.

960
01:43:04.436 --> 01:43:06.037
Right?

961
01:43:30.380 --> 01:43:31.860
Look over here.

962
01:43:34.155 --> 01:43:35.534
And a smile. please.

963
01:43:49.519 --> 01:43:50.479
Nozaki.

964
01:43:53.679 --> 01:43:54.920
The liverleaf!

965
01:44:08.250 --> 01:44:10.326
It's such a strong flower.

966
01:44:15.650 --> 01:44:17.771
It's just like Nozaki.

967
01:44:32.267 --> 01:44:34.151
With that injury.

968
01:44:34.600 --> 01:44:36.916
you are going to die here.

969
01:44:39.817 --> 01:44:40.974
Hey. Nozaki.

970
01:44:43.484 --> 01:44:45.665
Promise me that you'll live with me.

971
01:44:48.180 --> 01:44:50.371
I'll take you to the hospital.

972
01:44:53.720 --> 01:44:55.359
Let's live together.

973
01:44:59.033 --> 01:45:00.691
Your smile...

974
01:45:04.881 --> 01:45:06.705
I want to take one more picture.

975
01:48:21.369 --> 01:48:23.421
Oguro Taeko.

976
01:48:24.390 --> 01:48:25.460
Yes. sir.

977
01:48:29.455 --> 01:48:32.536
♪ The path ♪
<i>(hitori de)</i>

978
01:48:32.537 --> 01:48:34.883
♪ that I walked alone ♪
<i>(aruku)</i>

979
01:48:34.979 --> 01:48:36.256
Oguro Taeko.

980
01:48:36.353 --> 01:48:40.543
♪ turned the journey ♪
<i>(michi nori ga)</i>

981
01:48:40.544 --> 01:48:46.506
♪ into something sad ♪
<i>(sabishi monoda to)</i>

982
01:48:46.599 --> 01:48:51.750
♪ When I felt this ♪
<i>(kanjita toki)</i>

983
01:48:51.845 --> 01:48:57.667
♪ The living beings ♪
<i>(nukumori o motsu)</i>

984
01:48:57.668 --> 01:49:02.624
♪ that have warmth ♪
<i>(ikimono tachi wa)</i>

985
01:49:02.915 --> 01:49:08.288
♪ began to hold hands ♪
<i>(tagaini te o)</i>

986
01:49:08.289 --> 01:49:13.443
♪ began to hold hands ♪
<i>(tori hajimeru)</i>

987
01:49:34.038 --> 01:49:36.785
I'd like it if you always cut my hair.

988
01:49:41.801 --> 01:49:43.167
Nozaki...

989
01:49:44.426 --> 01:49:47.248
Let's go to Tokyo together.

990
01:50:03.288 --> 01:50:08.413
♪ If encounters change people ♪
<i>(deai ga hito)</i>

991
01:50:08.414 --> 01:50:13.422
♪ If encounters change people ♪
<i>(okaeru nonara)</i>

992
01:50:13.517 --> 01:50:18.611
♪ Then I haven't met you yet ♪
<i>(mada minu anata o)</i>

993
01:50:18.715 --> 01:50:23.494
♪ I will wait for you ♪
<i>(machimashou)</i>

994
01:50:23.846 --> 01:50:29.052
♪ The waters <i>(feelings)</i> ♪
<i>(karada o nagareru)</i>

995
01:50:29.403 --> 01:50:34.225
♪ that flow through my body ♪
<i>(mizu tachi wa)</i>

996
01:50:34.358 --> 01:50:39.715
♪ Don't let me hide lies ♪
<i>(jibun ni uso o)</i>

997
01:50:39.715 --> 01:50:45.157
♪ Don't let me hide lies ♪
<i>(tsukenaikara)</i>

998
01:50:47.494 --> 01:50:53.114
♪ Eventually. what I can see ♪
<i>(me ni mieru mono wa izure)</i>

999
01:50:53.994 --> 01:50:58.960
♪ Even if it disappears ♪
<i>(kieusete mo)</i>

1000
01:50:59.212 --> 01:51:04.929
♪ Continues to echo in your heart ♪
<i>(kokoro ni hibiku mono wa)</i>

1001
01:51:05.024 --> 01:51:08.958
♪ What remains... ♪
<i>(nokotte iku)</i>

1002
01:51:09.055 --> 01:51:13.526
♪ Divide and spread ♪
<i>(wakete kudasai)</i>

1003
01:51:13.623 --> 01:51:19.234
♪ your feelings ♪
<i>(anata no kimochi o)</i>

1004
01:51:23.887 --> 01:51:27.683
♪ If you're sad now ♪
<i>(ima kanashi nonara)</i>

1005
01:51:27.778 --> 01:51:32.655
♪ Let your tears flow here ♪
<i>(koko de namida o nagashi)</i>

1006
01:51:32.751 --> 01:51:36.535
♪ If you're happy now ♪
<i>(ima ureshii nonara)</i>

1007
01:51:36.634 --> 01:51:41.293
♪ Let's smile! ♪
<i>(waratte shimaou)</i>

1007
01:51:42.305 --> 01:52:42.461
